Between 50 and 100 million people are thought to have died in the pandemic, representing as much as 5% of the world's population. CAPE TOWN - This year marks the 100th anniversary of the influenza pandemic of 1918. Between 50 million and 100 million people are thought to have died in the pandemic, representing as much as 5% of the world's population. The flu pandemic has been a regular subject of speculation over the last century. Severe influenza epidemics tend to occur every few decades and experts believe that the next one is a question not of "if" but "when."